
To add files and directories to your .gitignore file, you just need to list them in the file so Git knows to ignore them when you commit changes. Hereâ€™s how to add the commonly ignored files related to deploying a Next.js project:

Create a .gitignore file (if you don't have one already): In the root directory of your project, create a file named .gitignore.

Add files and directories to the .gitignore file: You can add the following lines to .gitignore to ensure that unwanted files (like build artifacts and dependency directories) are ignored:

Common .gitignore Entries for Next.js:
bash
Copy code
# Dependency directories
node_modules/

# Build output (Next.js build)
.next/

# Logs
npm-debug.log*
yarn-debug.log*
yarn-error.log*


# Environment variables
.env
.env.local
.env.development
.env.test
.env.production

# Vercel-specific files (if you're deploying on Vercel)
.vercel/

# Next.js cache
.next/